social_posts.post_text: Christmas is my favorite time of year 🥰 Even with the hustle and bustle I want to bottle up the magical feeling. We experienced @enchantscottsdale and felt like we were in a @hallmarkchannel movie.  Fun fact… I grew up figure skating and became a professional coach in my late teens and twenties. I have a special place in my heart for ice skating. So glad my kids love it too!  #enchantscottsdalepartner #iwanttogoback

The kids got a little early Christmas cheer  with their new @amazonkids Fire Tablets #ad. With the busy holiday season, we love unwinding with some fun features they include, such as books and games. We love that the kids can also enjoy one of many educational apps with the one-year subscription of #AmazonKidsPlus each tablet comes with. Crew jams out to music, Ella loves to paint and color, and Beau gets so excited when he gets to play around with the learning games.

This Christmas was a special one. Back in our home and continued our family traditions. I know the hustle and bustle of the holidays can be a lot. But these are the moments I want my kids to remember. I may not be an everlasting memory to all. But I do want to leave a little magic to my kids' lives, and hopefully, when they get older and have kids of their own, they realize how amazing it is to create the magic.  Look at what some paper and some Christmas lights can do. It’s a feeling 🥹🥰 We didn’t get the Instagram family picture. But I sure soaked up Christmas Day. I hope you had a day filled with love. Xo

Making our favorite salmon meal with the Ninja Foodi NeverStick Possible Pan 4-qt. Pan from @Kohls. It does it all and so versatile. With the chaos of dinnertime in our household, simplifying the kitchen gadgets is key. #kohlsfinds #kohlspartner 

Salmon Recipe: 
1 pound of skinless boneless salmon 
1 tsp of garlic powder 
Sprinkle of salt 
Sprinkle of pepper 

Sauce ingredients:
1/4 cup of OJ 
1/3 cup of less sodium soy sauce 
1/2 cup of maple syrup 

Directions:
Season salmon with sprinkle of garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Sear salmon on medium heat until golden brown on each side. (may still be raw in the middle) Transfer to dish while making rice and sauce. In the same pan as cooking the salmon add the sauce ingredients on medium to low heat. Stir until the sauce reduces to coat a spoon. Add the salmon back to the pan and coat with the sauce. Finish cooking the salmon in 350 degree oven for 5-8 min depending on the size and thickness of your salmon filet. Plate with white rice, salmon, spoonful of sauce and eat with seaweed for some added flavor enjoy!!!!!

Spring break calls for sleeping in and making our favorite pancake hack using our Ninja Foodi Neverstick Possible Pan from @Kohls. It’s the yummiest and easiest to do! Pour your favorite pancake batter into your pan, and once you see it bubble, swirl in some syrup into your pancake. Let it cook a few seconds longer while you see the syrup soak in. Then flip your pancake and cook a few minutes longer. You will get the slight crunch from the caramelization of the syrup, and it’s mess free! It’s a win-win situation 🥰 Let me know if you ever try it, and be sure to pick up this pan if you do! #kohlsfinds #kohlspartner

Gimme that @FloridaOrangeJuice! We have Florida OJ in our household daily and we love incorporating it into busy weeknight recipes now that we’re back in our school routines. 100% OJ always finds its way into the kids lunches and even dinner recipes. Here’s my favorite salmon recipe that uses it - you have to try! It’s so easy!
 
Salmon Recipe:
1 cup of Florida OJ
1 pound of skinless boneless salmon
1 tsp of garlic powder
Sprinkle of salt
Sprinkle of pepper
Sauce ingredients:
1/3 cup of less sodium soy sauce
1/2 cup of maple syrup
 
Directions:
Season salmon with a sprinkle of garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Sear salmon on medium heat until golden brown on each side (may still be raw in the middle). Transfer to dish while making rice and sauce. In the same pan as the salmon, add the sauce ingredients on medium to low heat.
Stir until the sauce reduces to coat a spoon. Add the salmon back to the pan and coat with the sauce. Finish cooking the salmon in a 350-degree oven for 5-8 min depending on the size and thickness of your salmon filet. Plate with white rice, salmon, spoonful of sauce and eat with seaweed for some added flavor - enjoy!!!!
#FloridaOJ #TheOriginalWellnessDrink #ReadyforSchool #Sponsored
